author: Joshua Fluke
description:
RTO is officially “saving workplace culture” now… at least according to the Wall Street Journal, which seems to think your connective tissue is dissolving because you’re not sitting under fluorescent lighting anymore.

Today we’re looking at the latest corporate panic spiral: a full-blown essay arguing that remote work is destroying collaboration, innovation, trust, culture, the universe, and probably the ice caps too — all without showing a single statistic.

Because apparently…
Working from home and getting your work done?
That’s a problem.
But forcing everyone to commute, sit in hotel desks, and pretend to enjoy team-building yoga?
That’s “leadership,” baby.

• Why these RTO arguments are built entirely on vibes, not data
• The hilarious claim that “coffee badging” is killing companies
• Why bosses blame remote workers instead of learning to manage
